obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `MADRAS. — BOARD OF REVENUE.`
  line `A CT N O. X OF 18 49.`
  line `[ Passed on the 26 th May,1849. ]`
  line `Recites expediency of empowering G. to depute one Member of Board of Revenue to perform duties`
  line `of Board in any districts,&c.`
  line `1. Enacts, G. in C. of Fort St. G. may depute Member of Revenue Board to Perform in any district,`
  line `duties of Board collectively.`
  line `2, 3. Empowers Commissioner so deputed to exercise all powers mentioned in Commission,`
  line `( 3) Commission to be published in Gazette.`
  line `4. Correspondence,&c. under Commission to be deposited with and deemed Records of Board of`
  line Revenue.
  line `An Act for appointing a Commissioner of Revenue at Madras.`
  line `Whereas it is expedient that the Governor of Fort St. Georg e i n Cou ncil should be empowered to`
  line `depute a Member of the Board of Revenue, to perform in any of the Districts of that Presidency all or`
  line `any of the duties which, by the General Regulations and Laws of the Presidency, belong to the Board`
  line `of Revenue collectively, It is enacted as follows:`
  line `I. The Governor of Fort St. George in Council may, from time to time, whenever he shall see fit,`
  line `depute a member of the Board of Revenue t o perform alone, in any of the D istricts of that Presidency,`
  line `all or any of the duties which, by the General Regulations and Laws of the Presidency, belong to the`
  line `Board of Revenue collectively.`
  line `II. When a special Commission shall be given to a Member of the Board of Revenue under this`
  line `Act, the Member of the Board named therein shall, by vir tue thereof, be empowered to exercise,`
  line `within the limits of his Commission, all the powers and duties which by Law are vested in the Board`
  line `of Revenue collectively, without exception, or subject to any exceptions or restrictions, which shall be`
  line `prescribed i n such Commission; and all Regulations and Acts concerning the Board of Revenue shall`
  line `be deemed to apply to the said Commissioner within the limits of his Commission, and with regard to`
  line `all things concerning the Revenue of the Districts included in it, so far as is necessary to give full`
  line `effect to his Commission and to this Act.`
  line `III. Every such Commission shall be published in the Fort St. Ge o r ge Ga zette, and the`
  line `Commissioner shall enter on his Office from the date of such publication; and in like manner t he`
  line `revocation or other determination of any such Commission shall be published in the Fort St. George`
  line Gazette.
  line `IV. The correspondence and other documents belonging to any such Commission shall be`
  line `deposited on the determination there of, in the Office of th e Board of Revenue, and shall be deemed`
  line `records of the said Board.`
